column5: It's been sitting in the basement for 20 years , never worn, I have no use for it .
It would be great to wear to a game.
Not really. Unfortunately it was mass produced so there is many many out there
In the Garbage she goes!!
might wanna hold off a sec.  http://www.ebay.ca/itm/Toronto-Blue-Jays-WORLD-SERIES-Cap-Snapback-NWT-92-93-by-Annco-MLB-Vintage-Hat-/200918265639?pt=US_Hats&hash=item2ec7a96f27&_uhb=1#ht_500wt_1309
How about this one? 5 bucks anyone??
ill give you $4, final offer
LOL. If I bleach out the autograph, will you give me $7?  I wore it to one game. Now it's put away for my grandson some day.
#3 just scored potential winner so the jersey has gone up a couple of bucks I'd say
LOL. It's value goes up and down by the minute.
Take it to Chum Lee and see what he offers lol. "let me get a guy in in here who knows hats"lol
Give ya $100 for it .. I can always doante it to a good charity
Gonna pull it out of the closet and wear it in the bar in Terrace Bay for game 7 tomorrow night. Why not??

Have a #27 Corson Jersey here that Corson's mother had both him and Darcy Tucker sign (after Shayne was out of uniform) and then donate to a Crohn's auction. Also have a Gilmore Jersey.. signed...... dont' wear that Jersey Dan !  http://www.sportsmemorabilia.com/sports-products/dion-phaneuf-autographed-toronto-maple-leafs-jersey.html http://www.sportsmemorabilia.com/sports-products/dion-phaneuf-autographed-leafs-pro-jersey.html

Yea, I know it's worth a few bucks Wayne. As mentioned earlier, it will belong to my grandson some day. I will probably wear it tomorrow night though. It still has the holofoil on it and will still have it on after tomorrow night.
Don't spill too much beer on it.. or have a Bruins fan throw any at you! LOL
careful with the autograph, don't spill beer on it!
There will probably be about 6 other people in the bar besides me. All Leafs fans. And if I spill beer on my back and ruin the autograph, then I have big problems Wayne.
Again.. LOL.. Have fun my friend!
nice jersey Dan, here's mine from an older Leaf captain      hopefully the Bruins are still asleep tonight and the Leafs can eke out a win

I was going to say if you don't want it, you can donate it to a charity. We are having a dinner/auction on June 13 to support Big Brothers Big Sisters of Kawartha Lakes-Haliburton. Call them at 705-324-6800 if you would like to donate it.
